summary: 10 thoughts about the Good Omens Trailer
title: 10 thoughts about the Good Omens Trailer
body:
I have soooo  many thoughts about the trailer. so so so so so so many. i have tried to form as many of them into coherent thoughts as possible but i am also still Shaking a Lot so bear with me

1. I did not get the Hamm thing everyone was on about until this trailer. but now. I Get It.

2. Crowley’s fucking SMILE in the GARDEN OF EDEN KILL ME

3. What is the wall slamming????? I have to know!!!!!!!

4. Crowley and Aziraphale with Adam in the middle at the end is Fine, but like, if that’s a cop-out for C&A holding hands instead, I will Riot

5. every time michael sheen does anything is perfection

6. every frame of the bookshop scene fills me with agony

7. “TO THE WORLD” GOD PERFECT DELIVERY A++++ SEE #5

8. Similar to #4 if “Nice knowing you” is the substitute for “just enough of a bastard to be worth liking” I will also Riot

9. how the fuck are we supposed to wait until May 31st

10. oh y eah also “not my department” PFFFT Gabriel is the Lestrade of heaven and you can’t change my mind

summary:
I've watched new Good Omens trailer, and I saw several parallels with Supernatural! Here they are!
1) First of all, of course,...
body:
Hey, it’s time for parallels and references!

I’ve watched new Good Omens trailer, and I saw several parallels with Supernatural! Here they are!

1) First of all, of course, Crowleys. These charismatic, sarkastic, sassy, mischievous, villan-or-a-good-guy demons inhabit both universes – SPN and GO ones. Having read the boook of Pratchett-Gaiman I realized that my beloved King of Hell originates from there 😜👑 King Crowley wears sunglasses in 12x07 – that was a clear reference to his GO yellow-eyed fellow with the same name. 😎

2) Angels – Castiel and Aziraphale. There’s a scene in SPN 4x20 which reminded me of the one I saw in GO trailer. Here’s it 👼

2.1) Btw, Crowley-Azi relationships reminded me, first, of Crowley-Cas “Agent Beyonce-Agent Z” roleplay in s12 😁 Aaaand, of Destiel 😏😉 When Crowley hit poor old Azi against the wall. I do recall one or two scenes like that in SPN 😜 PS: I already ship Crowphale 😄

3) Heaven looks very much alike in both TV shows.

I wanted to do more but there’s this stupid limit – 10 images per post 👿 Ok, then I just say that in both TV shows there’s a character called Adam. Both of them have a connection with Hell but GO’s Adam is more like Noughat Child ™ nephilim Jack (GO’s Adam IS one, actually, and he is Heaven and Hell’s most wanted, huh). And he is NOT forgotten unlike poor kid Adam Milligan, the third Winchester brother who is still in Hell. Yikes…

Anyway, I’m sooo loking forward to see Good Omens! I will definetely love it ♥👼😈

P.S.: Not all the gifs are mine so all the credits go to gifmakers.

summary:
David Tennant and Michael Sheen star in the Good Omens official trailer. 

With Armageddon just days away, the armies of Heaven...
caption:
David Tennant and Michael Sheen star in the Good Omens official trailer.

With Armageddon just days away, the armies of Heaven and Hell are amassing and The Four Horsemen are ready to ride. Aziraphale, an angel, and Crowley, a demon, agree to join forces to find the missing Anti-Christ and to stop the war that will end everything. Based on the best-selling novel by Terry Pratchett and Neil Gaiman, Good Omens follows an unlikely duo and their quest to save the world. 

Worldwide premiere on Amazon Prime on May 31st 2019
